Terse, nearly incomprehensible details of changes to Eudora.RELEASE NOTESWarning--these are my change notes; they may mean little or nothing toyou.  I'm sorry I don't have the time to document these things morefully.1.3.1+ getting proper modifiers on arrow keys in TE+ fixed extra-long binhex filename bug+ making a nickname from a comp window now matches documentation+ finger now initially shows top, not bottom of scrolling list+ triangle shows if live nick is last in list+ option-Insert Recip now works correctly+ Can use change password over serial line+ Better about hanging up phone after cancels+ ICMP messages changed+ copying custom table from orig to reply (or forward or ...)+ spiffed about box a little+ added RFC 934 forward capability resources+ added reply one attribution resource+ @@ÄÄ fixed+ help key no longer inserts junk into messages.+ Sped up nickname window opening for large recip lists+ BinHex skipping whitespace+ Arranged for sender to be first recipient on reply all+ Changed CTB code to be tolerant of junk following digits in \D or \B+ Reduced time taken to open Nicknames window with a large recipient list+ Added flag for outgoing mail, using it when adding dates to forwards+ Fixed constant instead of QUOTE_LIMIT+ Fixed HNoPurge potential trouble in MommyMommy+ Changed invalid addresses to give 550 error code+ Adding Date: header when forwarding mail transferred from Out+ Revised UUCP system to 2-file sends+ Removed case sensitivity in month names+ Fixed problem with Out .toc and full disks+ Disallowing cmd-period autokey+ Fixed bug in About... box1.3+ Allowing a little junk at the end of binhex files1.3b126+ Fixed make nickname problem.1.3b125+ Not allowing dbl-click if command is down+ Cannot use nickname buttons to insert recips into sent message+ special mailbox flag handled properly after finder rename+ Fixed list display problem on New in Nickname window.+ Fixed some problems CTB error handling+ Fixed mailbox window mail folder bugs+ Fixed ForwardTo for comp windows+ Fixed mail folder deletion display bug+ Increased stack space by 4K+ Added HEX_PERMISSIVE preference for Palmer Station+ Fixed expand-tab-and-scroll-on-paste problem+ Fixed dashes and ligatures in Mac->usascii translation table1.3b119+ Fixed hiliting problem for narrow mailbox windows1.3b118+ Fixed logging of control chars+ Changed mail from and rcpt to commands to accommodate weird SMTP servers+ Changed alert logging to avoid DAStrings+ Tweaked icon bar display+ Disabling finger button when CTB in use1.3a116+ Out-xferred messages no longer confuse Include Self+ Fixed problem for single digit dates in UnixDate2Secs+ Fixed problem in UnloadUnneeded+ scroll bar overwrite by non-sub summary column+ empty From: reply all crash fixed+ Keyboard menu pacified+ Long nickname saving bug fixed+ Disappearing notes problem fixed+ Revised memory parameters+ allowing space as synonymn for ` in uuencode+ ph won’t fallback if IP address specified+ Error recovery from failed message open fixed+ Make Nickname with cbox selection fixed+ Voids in mailboxes fixed, at cost of some flicker.+ premature date truncation fixed+ MakeMessTitle problem with zero-width date/sender fixed.+ Fixed problem for wildly invalid hexbin filename+ Cmd-. now works for UUCP mail+ Tabs no longer modify sent messages.+ Made Ph be cmd-U+ Page Up & friends now work in nicknames window list box+ Tab now working properly in ph window+ Icon bar is now easier to click+ Read only alert is less aggressive+ Fixed problem with alert logging1.3b109	+ Put slop factor back in toc outdate calculations1.3b107+ New Nav escapes + \h pop hostname + \s smtp hostname + \Ddigits delay digits seconds + \eexpect-string look for expect-string in output+ UUCP envelope parsing overflow fixed+ reduced flicker in progress window+ finish nickname after return fixed+ removed fr table+ removed inverse lookup for hostname+ The TimeZone Of Death+ text removal from attachments not moving body up+ Re:<space><space>+ redraw on paste of long address list+ save current nickname on deactivate+ don’t remember open when memory low+ tables for ph+ arrows & scroll bars back again+ @host finger+ TCP close algorithm+ mailbox recalc after add+ italicize outgoing windows in Window menu1.3b102+ Large scrap handled more gracefully+ LC ethernet troubles (reduce WDS buffers with 8415)+ compaction problems fixed+ inverse lookup for HELO+ date stamp from envelope+ find now always autoscrolling to show found text+ type string, then cmd-G looks for old string fixed+ cmd-= no longer requires previous find+ ph, nicknames button outlines removed when not frontmost+ minimum size for ph window1.3b98+ segmentation improved+ Find always showing correct mailbox name in progress window+ Changed nicknames window button sizing+ Corrected (Unverified) code+ switched to X-Sender+ cmd-k no longer disappears notes+ using temp file for nickname saves (safer)+ scanning for .tmp files at startup+ NetRecvLine & TCP buffer tuning (2-3X performance increase for high latency POP connections)+ Compaction problem (crashes on mailbox closes)+ Changed EudoraTables file+ tab in first line of text block problem fixed+ extend easy delete to transfer of queued+ out of memory after divider drag+ error handling on reopens streamlined+ one more resize/scroll/scrollte bug fixed+ ph fallback+ Balloon help for ph+ safety for deja vu from old dirID+ enforce nickname length limit on new, rename+ fixed balloon help for some menus+ properly sending on timed checks+ Forward To of comp+ Foward from comp window+ first summaries of multi-parts being drawn+ incoming message window width adjusted properly+ last character of printed comp footer garbage removed+ save dialin pw properly+ no longer compacting old log+ alert timeouts working properly with new notify prefs+ won't get stuck on ICMP message+ password error messages changed+ Safety on compact after failed compact+ last shift-click problem+ change zon# resources to use strings for the timezone name+ numeric + date in timezones+ no longer looking at SHOW_SIZES1.3b93+ settings file version number fixed1.3b92+ aussie date problem+ weird finger servers+ type-to-select problem with one nickname as prefix of another+ message windows slightly too narrow+ uucp pathname length limit+ remove SYSTEM_SIZE+ don't allow 'STR ' overrides from system file+ ' ' restored after colon in From:+ turbo-mouse 2-click+ shift-select upwards ok in mailboxes+ option-space replaced with normal space on time in attribution+ check time bug fixed+ ‘STR ‘ overrides not allowed downstream of settings, either+ Time zone resource (zon#)+ balloon help for nickname list+ illegal nickname character warning alert+ catchup poll time after manual check+ h-scroll losing pixels+ Translit default bug fixed+ arrow-key autoscroll not moving bars in scrollte's+ comp shift-arrow autoscroll not working+ maildrop path not added for UUPCIn+ trim blank lines from replied sections+ Mailbox size display erroneously obeying show_size+ pw change failure not releasing connection (quinn)+ default outlines not being redrawn+ next still hilited when "find" in bg+ in not scrolling properly when last read and new mail comes+ scrollte resize bug fixed (AGAIN)+ balloon help for sort menu+ Make nickname probles with Out messages+ memory estimator problem+ connection timeout not immediately dying in SMTP1.3b90+ Fixed annoying In box bug in 1.3b89+ Fixed attempted log compaction in 1.3b891.3b89+ PgUp & friends now work in ph window+ PgUp & friends now work in message windows when sub editting+ Find window has become hot+ Find showing progress sooner+ Print menu enabling+ changed inbox-opening algorithm again+ insane numbers in size box during xfers eradicated+ Can quit from low mem alert+ FOND id for Mishawaka moved to 32256+ SendAgain copying flags from Out+ tolerating insane message heights+ find now ignores overlarge messages+ Print Selection menu item added+ need to limit alias names to 30 characters+ tolerate tab after colon in headers+ tweaked zooming+ made TCP cancellation much more aggressive+ paste from WP program often spurious "too big"+ changed default Translate In to be relatively transparent+ Triple-click difficulties fixed+ finalized switches dialog+ added auto-open+ forward from the Out mailbox+ DrawGrowIcon+ Made date display format uniform+ selectable transliteration tables+ shift-arrows and option-arrows, and shift-option arrows+ changed semantics of shift-click in mailboxes (now per HIG)+ mailbox column dividers are now draggable+ wrap menu item added+ guess paragraphs made smart about quoted sections+ added dialin user+ added finger button+ added don't xfer switch to new mailbox dlog+ Made GrowZone smart enough to nuke some unused windows+ compaction automatic on mailbox close, if 50% space wasted,  or if 5% of volume free space wasted+ Compact on Quit preference removed+ Tab expansion+ Find changed; cancel removed, Next is the default+ Fixed missed error code in POP+ priorities+ tweaked Bcc handling+ SMTP cancellation no longer botches POP close.+ wrap for quoted lines+ finger+ move new... back to transfer+ alerts won't timeout if you click or key in them+ scrolling subject field in messages instead of message+ finalized sender authentication+ Eudora can now change passwords, if your POP server cooperates+ make nickname item+ can use STR resources to override STR# resources+ added logging+ made messages use ste's (saves some code)+ changed select first unread behavior+ the world is now safe for cmd-f cmd-w+ made ph code use scrollte's (saved 1600 bytes of code)+ Clicking to: button now brings comp window forward+ segment unloading fixed+ not reconfiguring after Canc